.com%2Fsouth-korea-kim-byung-hoon-beauty-billionaire-kylie-jenner-fan-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epotential%20in%20the%20business%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20learned%20about%20Korean%20injectable%20products%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fred-flags-botox-filler-injections-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efillers%20and%20Botox%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20I%20decided%20to%20open%20a%20company%20in%20this%20area%20because%20of%20the%20high%20competitive%20edge%20and%20high%20barrier%20to%20entry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20four%20years%2C%20I%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstartup-founders-are-bootstrapping-instead-of-raising-money-from-vcs-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebootstrapped%20the%20company%3C%2Fa%3E.%20As%20a%20foreigner%20in%20Korea%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20a%20Caucasian%20foreigner%20%E2%80%94%20I%20stood%20out.%20Korean%20banks%20and%20early-stage%20investors%20were%20not%20interested%20in%20me%20or%20other%20foreigners%2C%20because%20they%20think%20we%20are%20risky%20to%20do%20business%20with.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20a%20foreigner%20opens%20a%20company%20here%2C%20it's%20almost%20impossible%20to%20get%20a%20loan%20from%20the%20bank%2C%20even%20if%20your%20company%20is%20profitable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20started%20pitching%20to%20investors%2C%20they%20told%20me%20they%20had%20never%20seen%20a%20foreigner%20pitch%20in%20Korean%20before.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20asking%20about%20the%20business%2C%20many%20asked%20more%20about%20me%3A%20Why%20was%20I%20doing%20business%20in%20Korea%3F%20If%20they%20invested%2C%20would%20I%20run%20away%20to%20Russia%20or%20Ukraine%3F%20The%20questions%20were%20somewhat%20ridiculous%20and%20childish.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228fe6e22e-8685-4726-baa0-38b3486f928f%5C%22%3ELearning%20'nunchi'%20taught%20me%20how%20to%20bridge%20Korean%20and%20foreign%20business%20culture%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Korea%2C%20there's%20a%20concept%20called%20%26quot%3Bnunchi%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvirtual-negotiations-research-backed-tactics-win-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eability%20to%20read%20the%20room%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20Asian%20culture%2C%20much%20of%20the%20meaning%20is%20conveyed%20through%20hints%2C%20tone%2C%20behavior%2C%20and%20atmosphere.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20was%20a%20student%2C%20I%20worked%20part-time%20as%20a%20business%20interpreter%20for%20foreigners%20coming%20to%20Korea.%20I%20noticed%20how%20impatient%20some%20of%20them%20would%20get%20during%20negotiations.%20Korean%20counterparts%20usually%20take%20longer%20to%20say%20yes%20or%20no.%20Sometimes%20they%20say%20yes%20in%20the%20meeting%2C%20but%20later%20change%20their%20minds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20me%2C%20I%20already%20felt%20the%20%26quot%3Bno%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20beginning%2C%20but%20they%20just%20said%20yes%20because%20they%20didn't%20want%20a%20confrontation.%20For%20my%20clients%2C%20it%20felt%20like%20a%20double-face.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNunchi%26quot%3B%20is%20a%20form%20of%20strategic%20intuition%20adapted%20to%20the%20Korean%20cultural%20code%2C%20where%20success%20often%20depends%20not%20on%20price%20or%20terms%2C%20but%20on%20knowing%20when%20to%20remain%20silent%2C%20when%20to%20yield%2C%20and%20when%20to%20stand%20firm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithout%20a%20certain%20level%20of%20%26quot%3Bnunchi%2C%26quot%3B%20it's%20very%20difficult%20to%20build%20a%20successful%20business%20in%20Korea.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20using%20my%20cultural%20knowledge%2C%20I%20can%20play%20a%20good%20role%20in%20bridging%20Korean%20products%20and%20technology%20with%20foreign%20markets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22aa7936dc-248a-4ee5-9812-7ee901a2192b%5C%22%3EHalf%20my%20life%20has%20been%20in%20Korea%20%E2%80%94%20and%20I'm%20now%20a%20citizen%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20lived%20in%20Korea%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-l