h%20Hemant%20Pandey%20and%20Vaashu%20Sharma.%20The%20couple%20moved%20from%20California%20to%20Bengaluru%20in%20November%202024.%20The%20essay%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%20Business%20Insider%20has%20verified%20their%20employment%20and%20compensation%20history.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EVaashu%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20I%20moved%20to%20the%20US%20for%20my%20master's%20in%202016%20after%20working%20in%20India%20for%20two%20years%20after%20my%20bachelor's.%20I%20had%20seen%20seniors%20from%20my%20course%20land%20exciting%20opportunities%20in%20tech%20in%20the%20US%2C%20and%20there%20seemed%20to%20be%20a%20lot%20more%20career%20options%20than%20I%20had%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20studied%20computer%20science%20at%20Stony%20Brook%20University%20in%20New%20York%2C%20and%20I%20met%20Hemant%20during%20our%20master's%20program.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHemant%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20I%20had%20also%20come%20to%20the%20US%20for%20similar%20reasons%2C%20but%20the%20plan%20was%20always%20to%20move%20back%20to%20India%20after%20a%20few%20years.%20We%20talked%20about%20it%20and%20were%20both%20aligned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20we%20graduated%20in%202017%2C%20Vaashu%20went%20on%20to%20work%20at%20IBM%2C%20Meta%2C%20and%20then%20Google.%20I%20worked%20at%20Tesla%2C%20SAP%2C%20Salesforce%2C%20and%20Meta.%20We%20got%20married%20in%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226ef82e3a-3759-4e1f-801b-6474d1dddf53%5C%22%3EThe%20itch%20to%20come%20home%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EVaashu%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EWhen%20we%20were%20discussing%20timelines%20for%20when%20we%20want%20to%20move%20back%2C%20my%20first%20thought%20was%2C%20do%20we%20want%20an%20X%20amount%20of%20money%3F%20That's%20when%20Hemant%20intervened%20and%20said%20that%20X%20would%20keep%20increasing%2C%20and%20we%20should%20not%20settle%20for%20a%20number.%20Instead%2C%20we%20picked%20a%20time%20and%20chose%202024%20as%20the%20year%20we%20would%20move%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHemant%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20I%20had%20so%20many%20reasons%20for%20wanting%20to%20move%20back%20%E2%80%94%20some%20logical%20and%20some%20emotional.%20I%20felt%20happier%20whenever%20I%20visited%20India%20for%20holidays.%20I%20also%20saw%20the%20crazy%20speed%20at%20which%20India%20was%20growing%20from%20when%20I%20had%20left.%20My%20friends%20back%20home%20were%20all%20making%20good%20money%2C%20and%20their%20lifestyle%20was%20just%20like%20ours%20was%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EVaashu%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20My%20biggest%20reason%20was%20that%20our%20family%20is%20based%20there%2C%20and%20I%20felt%20closer%20to%20the%20social%20and%20cultural%20values%20I%20was%20brought%20up%20with.%20I%20was%20also%20tired%20of%20missing%20big%20celebrations%20like%20my%20mother's%20retirement%2C%20my%20cousins'%20weddings%2C%20and%20being%20home%20for%20festivals.%20We%20were%20based%20in%20the%20Bay%20Area%2C%20and%20Indian%20festivals%20were%20celebrated%20with%20a%20lot%20of%20energy%2C%20but%20they%20could%20never%20match%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20second%20reason%20was%20how%20much%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Findians-leaving-big-tech-to-launch-startups-back-home-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EIndia's%20tech%20scene%20had%20changed%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20eight%20years%20since%20I%20had%20left.%20I%20saw%20a%20huge%20difference%20in%20the%20opportunities%20India%20had%20to%20offer%2C%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20number%20of%20teams%20Big%20Tech%20companies%20had%20in%20India%2C%20the%20products%20they%20were%20building%2C%20and%20the%20salaries%20they%20were%20offering%20to%20employees.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELastly%2C%20we%20had%20built%20a%20safety%20net%20in%20the%20US%20that%20we%20would%20be%20able%20to%20leverage%20in%20India.%20Knowing%20we%20won't%20have%20a%20financial%20crunch%20because%20of%20our%20savings%20gave%20me%20a%20lot%20of%20confidence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHemant%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D